title: Technical Interview Preparation (SWE)
description: Learn how to properly prepare for any technical interview, and all other helpful tips about the interview process. We will be discussing techniques from mock interviewing, technical assessment tips, interviewing, problem-solving skills, and more!
author: with Isaiah Bayas

title: Hacking with the browser
description: Learn what happens when you enter a URL in the browser, how to use APIs, how to get over $$$-walls, and familiarize yourself with the network tools in the browser. Everyone is welcome--please bring a laptop!
author: with Anna Lin

title: Introduction to Power Sources for Small Electronic Projects
description: A 2-3 hour session covering basic energy-related knowledge, how to use basic level power-related equipment (multimeters, power supplies, voltage, and current sensors, etc.), how to select the proper battery for your project, and commonly used battery options.
